quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  27,67,"And the ones who have disbelieved have said, \"When we are dust, and our fathers, surely will we indeed be brought out (of the graves)"
  27,68,"Indeed, we have already been promised this, we and our fathers earlier. Decidedly this is (nothing) except myths of the earliest (people)"
  27,69,"Say, \"Travel in the earth, then look into how was the end of the criminals"
  27,70,And do not grieve for them nor be straitened for what they scheme
  27,71,"And they say, \"When will this promise (come to pass), in case you are sincere"
  27,72,"Say, \"It may be that coming immediately after you is some (part) of that which you seek to hasten"
  27,73,And surely your Lord is indeed The Owner of Grace to mankind; but most of them do not thank (Him)
  27,74,And surely your Lord knows indeed whatever their breasts carefully secrete and whatever they make public
  27,75,And in no way is there an unseen thing in the heaven or the earth except that it is in an evident Book
  27,76,"Surely this Qur'an an narrates to the Seeds (Or: sons) of Israel most of that concerning which they differ"
  27,77,And surely it is indeed a guidance and a mercy to the believers
  27,78,"Surely our Lord will decree between them by His Judgment; and He is The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Knowing"
  27,79,So put your trust in Allah; surely you are upon the evident Truth
  27,80,"Surely you will not make the dead to hear, nor will you make the deaf to hear the call when they turn away, withdrawing"
  27,81,"And in no way will you ever guide the blind out of their errancy; decidedly you will make none to hear except the ones who believe in Our signs, (and) so they become Muslims (i.e., they surrender to Allah)"
  27,82,"And when the Saying befalls them, We will bring out for them from the earth a beast that will speak to them that mankind had no certitude in Our signs"